‚ÄòMy debut experience as a child actor was seamless and fun. I was very young, I guess about eight-nine years old and the shoot was in Ooty. I was asked if I would like to act in a film and I said ‚Äòwhy not‚Äô. So, I went to the location but I wasn‚Äôt tensed about it because my father was the director of the film. What unfolded was a beautiful experience that I vividly remember. It was amazing. I didn‚Äôt feel that there was a camera and I had to act. I credit all of this to my father,‚Äô says our May-June 2022 cover star @urstrulymahesh 

Superstar, noted actor and truly ‚ÄòA Star Unparalleled,‚Äô Mahesh Babu needs no formal introduction. A man of few and selectively important words, who mostly lets his films, actions and philanthropic deeds do all the talking, let‚Äôs loose and gets candid as he sits down for a conversation with our creative director @shanepeacock. The actor talks about how the perfectionist in him doesn‚Äôt let him settle for even an iota less, and why his next film is one of the most special ones in his career, amongst many other things.
